Build hook scripts are sourced in numeric order by build.sh.
Each script exposes well-known functions:

  usage_hook()      -- print one-line help entry
  clean_hook()      -- clean this component's outputs
  init_hook()       -- run at init stage (config/env setup)
  pre_build_hook()  -- run before build (configure, menuconfig, etc.)
  build_hook()      -- run at build stage
  post_build_hook() -- run after build (pack, release, etc.)

Scripts also declare which commands they handle:
  INIT_CMDS, PRE_BUILD_CMDS, BUILD_CMDS, POST_BUILD_CMDS

Execution order:
  00-config.sh   -- KConfig / defconfig management
  10-kernel.sh   -- kernel build
  25-amp.sh      -- AMP (HAL + RT-Thread) build
  30-rootfs.sh   -- Yocto rootfs build
  70-loader.sh   -- U-Boot / loader build
  80-firmware.sh -- firmware packaging
  99-all.sh      -- 'all' target, release

Chip-specific hooks can be added to:
  device/rockchip/rk3588/build-hooks/
They are executed before the common hooks for build/post-build stages
and after for init/pre-build stages.
